result.formatted_address: King Man House, Tai Nan St, Tong Mei, Hong Kong
result.name: Lander Hotel Prince Edward

reviews.text: The Lander Hotel is one of the better cost effective options in Hong Kong. It is a clean, neat and well managed hotel a bit of a walk away from the Prince Edward subway stop. It's a bit small but very comfortable once you are settled in. If you have large check, it will make it difficult to walk around but if you don't it will be perfect. The only other negatives I encountered were 1. It does not have gym despite it being listed as having one and 2. You must leave a deposit when you first arrive. Despite those concerns, it was a nice place with a helpful front desk that is worth your stay.

I stayed here on Chinese New Year, but even so the idea of paying more than $1000 per night in the most cramped hotel bar none is criminal. If that wasn't bad enough, I had to pay a deposit by credit card only (luckily my girlfriend had one), which I found very backward.

This is by far the smallest hotel room I've ever stayed anywhere in my entire life. The bathroom is so tiny that the shower curtain kept sticking to my back and arm. I decided to just not use the curtain and let the water flood the bathroom floor which is literally less than 1/2 square meter. I did book a room for one occupant and it is cheap. The location is convenient hence the train I gave two stars.
The hotel is tidy and has a nice aroma. When I went in my room, it was a bit small and I found to shower since it was tiny. The location was eight minutes of walking to a train station.

For a single room bathroom is extremely constraint in size limiting movement & room is small as well but clean. Small comparment that could fit 5 t-shirts max but only provided 3 hangers. Would be better to include hooks behind doors or wall for more hanging considering no proper wardrobe.
